analysisPopulations.name: Screened Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Screened Set includes all subjects who signed an informed consent form.
analysisPopulations.label: SCR
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Screened Set includes all subjects who signed an informed consent form.

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Full Analysis Set includes all enrolled subjects who received at least one dose of study drug.
analysisPopulations.label: FAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Full Analysis Set includes all enrolled subjects who received at least one dose of study drug.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Enrolled AND received >=1 dose of BIVV001

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Safety Set consists of all subjects who received at least one dose of study medication.
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Safety Set consists of all subjects who received at least one dose of study medication.

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacokinetic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: Subjects with evaluable PK samples; includes at least 16 participants in Arm A participating in the sequential PK subgroup undergoing extensive PK sampling at Baseline and Week 26, and other participants undergoing abbreviated PK sampling.
analysisPopulations.label: PK Set
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Subjects with evaluable PK samples; includes at least 16 participants in Arm A participating in the sequential PK subgroup undergoing extensive PK sampling at Baseline and Week 26, and other participants undergoing abbreviated PK sampling.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received BIVV001 AND has evaluable PK samples

analysisPopulations.name: Surgery Subgroup
analysisPopulations.text: Participants from any arm who undergo major surgery during the study to assess control and prevention of bleeding with BIVV001 treatment in the surgical setting.
analysisPopulations.label: Surgery
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Participants from any arm who undergo major surgery during the study to assess control and prevention of bleeding with BIVV001 treatment in the surgical setting.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Enrolled AND undergo major surgery during study period

characteristics.name: Age
characteristics.description: Age at baseline in years (>=12 years of age for inclusion)

characteristics.name: Endogenous FVIII activity
characteristics.description: Baseline endogenous FVIII activity level (severe hemophilia A defined as <1 IU/dL)

characteristics.name: Annualized Bleeding Rate
characteristics.description: Historical or study-period annualized bleeding rate (ABR)
